Furthermore, as illustrated in Fig. 7
                        , the secondary effluent significantly inhibited the DDVP removal with kobs of 0.038 and 0.019 min−1 compared to those of 0.306 and 0.132 min−1 in O3/SPC and O3 control (deionized water) systems, respectively. Note that there is recalcitrant organic matters in the secondary effluent (wastewater characteristics in Table 1
